      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake the layers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 175°C conventional. Grease and line three 23 cm round tins (or bake in two batches if you have only two). Whisk flour, sugar, bicarbonate of soda, cinnamon, and salt in a large bowl. Make a well in the centre and add the eggs, oil, and vanilla; stir with a spatula just until combined. Fold in the mashed banana, drained pineapple, and chopped pecans. Divide the batter between the tins and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until a skewer comes out clean. Cool in the tins for 10 minutes, then turn onto racks.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the frosting",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the cream cheese and softened butter together until smooth and no lumps remain. Add the sifted icing sugar in three additions, beating on low speed until incorporated, then increase to medium and beat for 1 minute. Add the vanilla extract. The frosting should be thick enough to spread without running. If it is too soft, refrigerate for 15 to 20 minutes before using.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ensure the cake layers are fully cool before frosting. Place the first layer on a serving plate and spread a generous amount of frosting over the top. Add the second layer and repeat, then place the third layer on top. Spread the remaining frosting over the top and sides of the cake, using an icing spatula for a smooth or textured finish. Decorate the top with the reserved pecan halves. Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving to allow the frosting to set.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
